==English==
===Etymology===
From {{L.}} noun of action ''[[actio]]'', ‘doing’ or ‘making’, from [[perfect passive participle]] ''[[actus]]'', ‘deed’, from verb ''[[agere]]'', ‘do’, + action suffix ''[[-io]]''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-action.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|ækʃən}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}} 

# Something [[done]] so as to accomplish a [[purpose]].
# A way of [[motion]] or functioning.
#* ''Knead bread with a rocking '''action'''.''
# A fast-paced [[activity]].
#* ''an '''action''' movie''
# A [[mechanism]]; a moving [[part]] or [[assembly]].
#* ''a rifle '''action'''''
# {{music}}: The set of moving mechanical parts in a [[keyboard]] instrument which transfer the motion of the [[key]] to the sound-making [[device]].
# {{slang}}: [[sexual|Sexual]] activity; [[intercourse]].
#* ''She gave him some '''action'''.''
# The distance separating the [[strin]]gs and the [[fretboard]] on the [[guitar]].
# {{military}} [[combat|Combat]].
#* ''He saw some '''action''' in the Korean War.''
# {{law}} A [[charge]] or other process in a law court.

